News Corp. (NWSA)  Chairman and Chief
Executive Officer  Rupert Murdoch  and his son, James, spent three
hours defending the company’s handling of the News of the World
phone-hacking scandal yesterday.  Following are their answers to the central questions put to
them by the said at a Culture, Media and Sport Committee hearing
in London:  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Hutton in London at 
 rhutton1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
